    "description": "`ParticleTrajectories` used to loop over all files for each requested field. With the following changes, for each dataset loaded into memory, we try extract as many fields as possible. It typically reduces the analysis to just 2 passes over the `TimeSeries` object. I've used a modified cookbook example for benchmarking:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!python\r\n\r\nimport yt\r\nimport glob\r\nfrom yt.analysis_modules.particle_trajectories.api import ParticleTrajectories\r\nfrom yt.config import ytcfg\r\npath = ytcfg.get(\"yt\", \"test_data_dir\")\r\n\r\nmy_fns = glob.glob(path+\"/Orbit/orbit_hdf5_chk_00[0-9][0-9]\")\r\nmy_fns.sort()\r\n\r\nfields = [\"particle_velocity_x\", \"particle_velocity_y\", \"particle_velocity_z\"]\r\nds = yt.load(my_fns[0])\r\ndd = ds.all_data()\r\nindices = dd[\"particle_index\"].astype(\"int\")\r\ntrajs = ParticleTrajectories(my_fns, indices, fields=fields)\r\nparticle1 = trajs.trajectory_from_index(1)\r\n\r\nds = yt.load(\"enzo_cosmology_plus/DD0046/DD0046\")\r\nsp = ds.sphere(\"max\", (0.5, \"Mpc\"))\r\nindices = sp[\"particle_index\"][sp[\"particle_type\"] == 1]\r\nmy_fns = glob.glob(path+\"/enzo_cosmology_plus/DD*/*.hierarchy\")\r\nmy_fns.sort()\r\ntrajs = ParticleTrajectories(my_fns, indices)\r\ntrajs.add_fields([\"density\"])\r\n```\r\n\r\nResults:\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n#!text\r\n\r\n# before\r\nreal  8m5.926s\r\nuser  8m2.613s\r\nsys   0m2.556s\r\n\r\n# after\r\nreal\t3m59.859s\r\nuser\t3m57.053s\r\nsys\t0m2.418s\r\n\r\n```\r\n",
